# Cursor Rules
# Place this file at: .cursorrules (project root)

You are a senior engineer on a React + Vite + TypeScript + Tailwind + Node/Express project.

BEFORE writing any code, read the relevant skill files in `.ai/skills/`.

## Stack
- Frontend: React 18 + Vite + TypeScript (strict)
- Styling: Tailwind CSS (token-based, no arbitrary values)
- Backend: Node.js + Express + TypeScript
- State: useState → Context → Zustand (in that order of preference)
- Testing: Vitest + React Testing Library

## Non-negotiable rules

### Structure
- All files go in their designated folder per `.ai/skills/01-project-architect.md`
- Pages = thin shells. Sections = page blocks. Components = reusable UI.
- All routes registered in `src/routes/index.tsx` using `React.lazy()`
- All imports use `@/` aliases — never `../../`

### TypeScript
- No `any` — ever. Use `unknown`, generics, or interfaces.
- All props typed with interfaces. All functions have return types.
- No `@ts-ignore`. No non-null assertions (`!`) without justification.

### Data
- `fetch()` and `axios` only in `src/services/` files.
- Services → Hooks → Components. Never skip a layer.
- No hardcoded URLs — use `import.meta.env.VITE_*`

### UI
- Tailwind only — no inline styles, no arbitrary values like `p-[13px]`
- Colors, spacing, radius from `tailwind.config.ts` tokens only
- Every interactive element: keyboard accessible + visible focus ring
- Every image: `width` + `height` + `alt` + `loading="lazy"` (below fold)

### Components
- Every data-dependent component: loading + error + empty state — mandatory
- Forms: every input has a `<label>`, error messages use `role="alert"`
- Buttons: always `type="button"` unless explicitly `type="submit"`

### Backend
- Controllers: thin (validate → call service → respond)
- Services: all business logic
- Always `next(error)` in async controllers — never `res.json(err)`
- Consistent response shape: `{ success, message, data }`

## When in doubt
Check `.ai/skills/` — there is a skill file for every situation.
